race.comment: CAPITAL DIVA (4) brought strong form to resumption and raced forward when beaten just 1L over 1100m at Ipswich  Has been kept on the fresh side and maps for the run of the race. She has more to offer and can take this out with the extra fitness.  INTRECCIATO (12) twice missed a nose at the Gold Coast before being outgraded at Doomben. Much better suited and rates right up to this. She can feature with average luck in the run. HOME ZONE (6) was plainer here last time but was good winning a CL1 at the track prior. That sort of form would have her in the frame and she jumps from an inside barrier. DECORATIVE (11) resumes for the Currie yard and is worth a betting watch.
